                <div class=3D"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break=
-words light"><p data-start=3D"0" data-end=3D"285"><strong data-start=3D"0"=
 data-end=3D"15">Web cookies</strong> (also called <strong data-start=3D"29=
" data-end=3D"45">HTTP cookies</strong>, <strong data-start=3D"47" data-end=
=3D"66">browser cookies</strong>, or simply <strong data-start=3D"78" data-=
end=3D"89">cookies</strong>) are small pieces of data that websites store o=
n your device (computer, phone, etc.) through your web browser. They are us=
ed to remember information about you and your interactions with the site.</=
p>
<h3 data-start=3D"287" data-end=3D"310">Purpose of Cookies:</h3>
<ol data-start=3D"311" data-end=3D"651">
<li data-start=3D"311" data-end=3D"456">
<p data-start=3D"314" data-end=3D"339"><strong data-start=3D"314" data-end=
=3D"336">Session Management</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"343" data-end=3D"456">
<li data-start=3D"343" data-end=3D"368">
<p data-start=3D"345" data-end=3D"368">Keeping you logged in</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"372" data-end=3D"412">
<p data-start=3D"374" data-end=3D"412">Remembering items in a shopping cart=
</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"416" data-end=3D"456">
<p data-start=3D"418" data-end=3D"456">Saving language or theme preferences=
</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"458" data-end=3D"547">
<p data-start=3D"461" data-end=3D"483"><strong data-start=3D"461" data-end=
=3D"480">Personalization</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"487" data-end=3D"547">
<li data-start=3D"487" data-end=3D"547">
<p data-start=3D"489" data-end=3D"547">Tailoring content or ads based on yo=
ur previous activity</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"549" data-end=3D"651">
<p data-start=3D"552" data-end=3D"579"><strong data-start=3D"552" data-end=
=3D"576">Tracking &amp; Analytics</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"583" data-end=3D"651">
<li data-start=3D"583" data-end=3D"651">
<p data-start=3D"585" data-end=3D"651">Monitoring browsing behavior for ana=
lytics or marketing purposes</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start=3D"653" data-end=3D"656" aria-hidden=3D"true">
<h3 data-start=3D"658" data-end=3D"679">Types of Cookies:</h3>
<ol data-start=3D"680" data-end=3D"1239">
<li data-start=3D"680" data-end=3D"833">
<p data-start=3D"683" data-end=3D"705"><strong data-start=3D"683" data-end=
=3D"702">Session Cookies</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"709" data-end=3D"833">
<li data-start=3D"709" data-end=3D"759">
<p data-start=3D"711" data-end=3D"759">Temporary; deleted when you close yo=
ur browser</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"763" data-end=3D"833">
<p data-start=3D"765" data-end=3D"833">Used for things like keeping you log=
ged in during a single session</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"835" data-end=3D"996">
<p data-start=3D"838" data-end=3D"863"><strong data-start=3D"838" data-end=
=3D"860">Persistent Cookies</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"867" data-end=3D"996">
<li data-start=3D"867" data-end=3D"934">
<p data-start=3D"869" data-end=3D"934">Stored on your device until they exp=
ire or are manually deleted</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"938" data-end=3D"996">
<p data-start=3D"940" data-end=3D"996">Used for remembering login credentia=
ls, settings, etc.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"998" data-end=3D"1078">
<p data-start=3D"1001" data-end=3D"1027"><strong data-start=3D"1001" data-e=
nd=3D"1024">First-Party Cookies</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1031" data-end=3D"1078">
<li data-start=3D"1031" data-end=3D"1078">
<p data-start=3D"1033" data-end=3D"1078">Set by the website you're visiting=
 directly</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1080" data-end=3D"1239">
<p data-start=3D"1083" data-end=3D"1109"><strong data-start=3D"1083" data-e=
nd=3D"1106">Third-Party Cookies</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1113" data-end=3D"1239">
<li data-start=3D"1113" data-end=3D"1183">
<p data-start=3D"1115" data-end=3D"1183">Set by other domains (usually adve=
rtisers) embedded in the website</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1187" data-end=3D"1239">
<p data-start=3D"1189" data-end=3D"1239">Commonly used for tracking across =
multiple sites</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
                </div>
                <div class=3D"tab-pane fade" id=3D"v-pills-profile" role=3D=
"tabpanel" aria-labelledby=3D"v-pills-profile-tab" tabindex=3D"0">
                    <div class=3D"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full b=
reak-words light"><p data-start=3D"0" data-end=3D"149"><strong data-start=
=3D"0" data-end=3D"26">Authentication cookies</strong> are a special type o=
f web cookie used to <strong data-start=3D"68" data-end=3D"91">identify and=
 verify</strong> a user after they log in to a website or web application.<=
/p>
<hr data-start=3D"151" data-end=3D"154" aria-hidden=3D"true">
<h3 data-start=3D"156" data-end=3D"180">What They Do:</h3>
<p data-start=3D"181" data-end=3D"331">Once you log in to a site, the serve=
r creates an authentication cookie and sends it to your browser. This cooki=
e:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"333" data-end=3D"503">
<li data-start=3D"333" data-end=3D"378">
<p data-start=3D"335" data-end=3D"378">Proves to the website that you're lo=
gged in</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"379" data-end=3D"445">
<p data-start=3D"381" data-end=3D"445">Prevents you from having to log in a=
gain on every page you visit</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"446" data-end=3D"503">
<p data-start=3D"448" data-end=3D"503">Can persist across sessions if you s=
elect "Remember me"</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"505" data-end=3D"508" aria-hidden=3D"true">
<h3 data-start=3D"510" data-end=3D"560">What's Inside an Authentication Coo=
kie?</h3>
<p data-start=3D"561" data-end=3D"584">Typically, it contains:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"586" data-end=3D"698">
<li data-start=3D"586" data-end=3D"638">
<p data-start=3D"588" data-end=3D"638">A <strong data-start=3D"590" data-en=
d=3D"611">unique session ID</strong> (not your actual password)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"639" data-end=3D"698">
<p data-start=3D"641" data-end=3D"698">Optional metadata (e.g., expiration =
time, security flags)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
                </div>
                <div class=3D"tab-pane fade" id=3D"v-pills-analytics" role=
=3D"tabpanel" aria-labelledby=3D"v-pills-analytics-tab" tabindex=3D"0">
                    <div class=3D"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full b=
reak-words light"><p data-start=3D"0" data-end=3D"215"><strong data-start=
=3D"0" data-end=3D"21">Analytics cookies</strong> are cookies used to <stro=
ng data-start=3D"42" data-end=3D"101">collect data about how visitors inter=
act with a website</strong>. Their primary purpose is to help website owner=
s understand and improve user experience by analyzing things like:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"217" data-end=3D"377">
<li data-start=3D"217" data-end=3D"248">
<p data-start=3D"219" data-end=3D"248">How users navigate the site</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"249" data-end=3D"287">
<p data-start=3D"251" data-end=3D"287">Which pages are most/least visited</=
p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"288" data-end=3D"324">
<p data-start=3D"290" data-end=3D"324">How long users stay on each page</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"325" data-end=3D"377">
<p data-start=3D"327" data-end=3D"377">What device, browser, or location th=
e user is from</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"379" data-end=3D"382" aria-hidden=3D"true">
<h3 data-start=3D"384" data-end=3D"411">What They Track:</h3>
<p data-start=3D"412" data-end=3D"464">Some examples of data analytics cook=
ies may collect:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"466" data-end=3D"713">
<li data-start=3D"466" data-end=3D"504">
<p data-start=3D"468" data-end=3D"504">Page views and time spent on pages</=
p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"505" data-end=3D"555">
<p data-start=3D"507" data-end=3D"555">Click paths (how users move from pag=
e to page)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"556" data-end=3D"609">
<p data-start=3D"558" data-end=3D"609">Bounce rate (users who leave without=
 interacting)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"610" data-end=3D"660">
<p data-start=3D"612" data-end=3D"660">User demographics (location, languag=
e, device)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"661" data-end=3D"713">
<p data-start=3D"663" data-end=3D"713">Referring websites (how users arrive=
d at the site)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
                </div>
                <div class=3D"tab-pane fade" id=3D"v-pills-optout" role=3D"=
tabpanel" aria-labelledby=3D"v-pills-optout-tab" tabindex=3D"0">
<div class=3D"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light">
<p data-start=3D"372" data-end=3D"426">Here=E2=80=99s how you can disable c=
ookies in common browsers:</p>
<h3 data-start=3D"428" data-end=3D"452">1. Google Chrome</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"453" data-end=3D"782">
<li data-start=3D"453" data-end=3D"525">
<p data-start=3D"455" data-end=3D"525">Open Chrome and click the three vert=
ical dots in the top-right corner.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"526" data-end=3D"608">
<p data-start=3D"528" data-end=3D"608">Go to <strong data-start=3D"534" dat=
a-end=3D"546">Settings</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"549" data-end=3D=
"573">Privacy and security</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"576" data-en=
d=3D"607">Cookies and other site data</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"609" data-end=3D"782">
<p data-start=3D"611" data-end=3D"640">Choose your preferred option:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"643" data-end=3D"782">
<li data-start=3D"643" data-end=3D"710">
<p data-start=3D"645" data-end=3D"710"><strong data-start=3D"645" data-end=
=3D"666">Block all cookies</strong> (not recommended, can break most websit=
es).</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"713" data-end=3D"782">
<p data-start=3D"715" data-end=3D"782"><strong data-start=3D"715" data-end=
=3D"744">Block third-party cookies</strong> (can block ads and tracking coo=
kies).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"784" data-end=3D"810">2. Mozilla Firefox</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"811" data-end=3D"1085">
<li data-start=3D"811" data-end=3D"887">
<p data-start=3D"813" data-end=3D"887">Open Firefox and click the three hor=
izontal lines in the top-right corner.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"888" data-end=3D"934">
<p data-start=3D"890" data-end=3D"934">Go to <strong data-start=3D"896" dat=
a-end=3D"908">Settings</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"911" data-end=3D=
"933">Privacy &amp; Security</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"935" data-end=3D"1085">
<p data-start=3D"937" data-end=3D"1085">Under the <strong data-start=3D"947=
" data-end=3D"979">Enhanced Tracking Protection</strong> section, choose <s=
trong data-start=3D"996" data-end=3D"1006">Strict</strong> to block most co=
okies or <strong data-start=3D"1032" data-end=3D"1042">Custom</strong> to m=
anually choose which cookies to block.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"1087" data-end=3D"1104">3. Safari</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1105" data-end=3D"1315">
<li data-start=3D"1105" data-end=3D"1177">
<p data-start=3D"1107" data-end=3D"1177">Open Safari and click <strong data=
-start=3D"1129" data-end=3D"1139">Safari</strong> in the top-left corner of=
 the screen.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1178" data-end=3D"1216">
<p data-start=3D"1180" data-end=3D"1216">Go to <strong data-start=3D"1186" =
data-end=3D"1201">Preferences</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"1204" dat=
a-end=3D"1215">Privacy</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1217" data-end=3D"1315">
<p data-start=3D"1219" data-end=3D"1315">Check <strong data-start=3D"1225" =
data-end=3D"1246">Block all cookies</strong> to stop all cookies, or select=
 options to block third-party cookies.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"1317" data-end=3D"1342">4. Microsoft Edge</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1343" data-end=3D"1614">
<li data-start=3D"1343" data-end=3D"1415">
<p data-start=3D"1345" data-end=3D"1415">Open Edge and click the three hori=
zontal dots in the top-right corner.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1416" data-end=3D"1508">
<p data-start=3D"1418" data-end=3D"1508">Go to <strong data-start=3D"1424" =
data-end=3D"1436">Settings</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"1439" data-e=
nd=3D"1472">Privacy, search, and services</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=
=3D"1475" data-end=3D"1507">Cookies and site permissions</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1509" data-end=3D"1614">
<p data-start=3D"1511" data-end=3D"1614">Select your cookie settings from t=
here, including blocking all cookies or blocking third-party cookies.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"1616" data-end=3D"1650">5. On Mobile (iOS/Android)</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1651" data-end=3D"1873">
<li data-start=3D"1651" data-end=3D"1753">
<p data-start=3D"1653" data-end=3D"1753">For Safari on iOS: Go to <strong d=
ata-start=3D"1678" data-end=3D"1690">Settings</strong> &gt; <strong data-st=
art=3D"1693" data-end=3D"1703">Safari</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"1=
706" data-end=3D"1728">Privacy &amp; Security</strong> &gt; <strong data-st=
art=3D"1731" data-end=3D"1752">Block All Cookies</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1754" data-end=3D"1873">
<p data-start=3D"1756" data-end=3D"1873">For Chrome on Android: Open the ap=
p, tap the three dots, go to <strong data-start=3D"1819" data-end=3D"1831">=
Settings</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"1834" data-end=3D"1858">Privac=
y and security</strong> &gt; <strong data-start=3D"1861" data-end=3D"1872">=
Cookies</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"1875" data-end=3D"1888">Be Aware:</h3>
<p data-start=3D"1889" data-end=3D"2129">Disabling cookies can make your on=
line experience more difficult. Some websites may not load properly, or you=
 may be logged out frequently. Also, certain features may not work as expec=
ted.</p>
</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
